%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Al-Azizia%20case%3A%20Nawaz%20Sharif's%20sentence%20suspended%2C%20reports%20say%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698140906000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104672668%2Cimgsize-56560.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fal-azizia-case-nawaz-sharifs-sentence-suspended-reports-say%2Farticleshow%2F104672648.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Confirming%20the%20Punjab%20cabinet's%20move%2C%20caretaker%20information%20minister%20Aamir%20Mir%20told%20the%20Pakistan-based%20media%20outlet%20that%20the%20decision%20was%20taken%20while%20exercising%20its%20constitutional%20powers%20under%20Section%20401%20of%20the%20Criminal%20Procedural%20Code%20(CPC)%2C%20which%20also%20authorises%20it%20to%20pardon%20any%20offender.%20The%20approval%20was%20given%20through%20a%20circulation%20summary.%20%26quot%3BThe%20final%20decision%20of%20the%20case%20will%20be%20taken%20by%20the%20court%20itself%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20The%20Pakistan%20Muslim%20League-Nawaz%20(PML-N)%20supremo%20was%20sentenced%20by%20an%20accountability%20court%20in%20both%20the%20Avenfield%20and%20Al-Azizia%20Steel%20Mills%20cases.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20sad%2C%20lonely%20secret%20behind%20America's%20never-ending%20wave%20of%20Marvel%20movies%20and%20Disney%20reboots%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20conga%20line%20of%20franchise%20characters.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536cd0096f7540cd0635163%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMedia%20companies%20are%20in%20the%20business%20of%20selling%20nostalgia%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20because%20Americans%20are%20lonely.%3Cp%3EJoanne%20Joo%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202010%2C%20the%20Walt%20Disney%20Company%20remade%20%26quot%3BAlice%20in%20Wonderland%3Cem%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20kicking%20off%20a%20run%20of%2014%20live-action%20remakes%20of%20their%20animated%20classics%20that%20would%20gross%20the%20company%20%243.2%20billion%20at%20the%20domestic%20box%20office%20over%20the%20following%20decade.%20That%20same%20year%2C%20eyeing%20the%20coming%20conclusion%20of%20their%20%26quot%3BHarry%20Potter%26quot%3B%20film%20franchise%2C%20Warner%20Bros.%20struck%20a%20deal%20to%20have%20an%20entire%20section%20of%20Universal's%20Orlando%20resort%20built%20out%20into%20The%20Wizarding%20World%20of%20Harry%20Potter%2C%20beginning%20a%20brisk%2C%20decade-long%20trade%20of%20selling%20millennials%20plastic%20wands%20and%20color-coded%20apparel%20and%20homewares.%20One%20year%20later%2C%20Sony%20would%20reboot%20the%20%26quot%3BSpider-Man%26quot%3B%20franchise%2C%20Fox%20would%20reboot%20the%20%26quot%3BX-Men%26quot%3B%20franchise%2C%20and%20two%20years%20after%20that%20DC%20would%20reboot%20the%20%26quot%3BSuperman%26quot%3B%20franchise.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20wave%20of%20reboots%20and%20revivals%20was%20not%20a%20coincidence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20major%2C%20connecting%20way%20that%20these%20financial%20entities%20are%20able%20to%20capitalize%20on%20our%20emotions%20%E2%80%94%20be%20it%20through%20movie%20remakes%20or%20toys%20or%20a%20Tasmanian%20Devil%20ashtray%20%E2%80%94%20is%20by%20appealing%20to%20nostalgia.%20It's%20a%20complex%20emotion%2C%20but%20attempts%20to%20harness%20(or%20exploit)%20nostalgia%20are%20one%20of%20the%20key%20drivers%20behind%20the%20vast%20business%20juggernaut%20that%20is%20the%20pop%20culture%20industry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20precise%20%26quot%3Bwhy%26quot%3B%20of%20nostalgia%20is%20murky.%20But%20we%20know%20that%2C%20time%20and%20again%2C%20nostalgia%20drives%20people%20to%20spend%20unfathomable%20amounts%20of%20money%20on%20things%20they%20liked%20as%20a%20kid.%20What's%20the%20thinking%20behind%20spending%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20on%20a%20single%20animation%20cell%20from%20a%20show%20you%20liked%20when%20you%20were%20young%3F%20Why%20did%20an%20entire%20generation%20plow%20the%20affluence%20they%20came%20into%20in%20the%20'90s%20into%20household%20goods%20and%20apparel%20derived%20from%20shows%20they%20watched%20while%20munching%20cereal%20on%20Saturday%20mornings%3F%20Why%2C%20despite%20a%20college%20degree%2C%20despite%20a%20revulsion%20for%20nearly%20everything%20the%20former%20richest%20woman%20in%20England%20believes%20about%20gender%2C%20despite%20a%20good%20life%20and%20career%20and%20general%20satisfaction%2C%20why%20on%20earth%20does%20a%20real%20part%20of%20me%20still%20yearn%20for%20a%20personalized%20letter%20inviting%20me%20to%20Hogwarts%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20of%20why%20nostalgia%20is%20able%20to%20get%20its%20hooks%20so%20deep%20into%20younger%20generations%20may%20come%20down%20to%20another%20emotion%3A%20loneliness.%20Around%20the%20same%20time%20as%20the%20emergence%20of%20reboots%2C%20studies%20found%20that%20young%20people%20were%20reporting%20levels%20of%20loneliness%20that%20had%20not%20been%20seen%20in%20decades.%20As%20we%20became%20more%20disconnected%20from%20the%20people%20around%20us%2C%20we%20sought%20out%20comfort%20in%20other%20ways.%20If%20the%20key%20driver%20of%20reboots%20is%20nostalgia%20%E2%80%94%20then%20the%20key%20driver%20of%20nostalgia%20is%20loneliness.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20lonely%20roots%20of%20nostalgia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20series%20of%20studies%20out%20of%20Southampton%20University%20published%20in%20the%20Journal%20of%20Personality%20and%20Social%20Psychology%20in%202006%20sought%20to%20understand%20nostalgia%20through%20a%20series%20of%20experiments.%20In%20one%2C%20drawing%20on%20a%20sample%20of%2043%20students%2C%20researchers%20tried%20to%20figure%20out%20if%20there%20was%20a%20link%20between%20loneliness%20and%20feelings%20of%20nostalgia.%20The%20subjects%20were%20asked%20to%20take%20a%20test%20to%20calculate%20their%20score%20on%20the%20UCLA%20Loneliness%20Scale%2C%20a%20quick%20assessment%20that%20asks%20people%20how%20often%20they%20feel%20disconnected%20from%20others%2C%20such%20as%20how%20often%20they%20feel%20alone%2C%20or%20starved%20for%20company%2C%20or%20find%20it%20difficult%20to%20make%20friends.%20Researchers%20then%20informed%20each%20participant%20of%20their%20score%20and%20whether%20it%20indicated%20things%20like%20a%20high%20or%20low%20degree%20of%20loneliness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20participants%20took%20Batcho's%20Nostalgia%20Inventory%2C%20a%20psychological%20test%20developed%20by%20Krystine%20Batcho%20in%201995%20to%20quantify%20how%20deeply%20people%20feel%20nostalgia%20at%20a%20given%20time.%20It's%20a%20questionnaire%20where%20respondents%20select%20a%20number%20between%201%20and%209%20(1%20indicating%20%26quot%3Bnot%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%209%20meaning%20%26quot%3Bvery%20much%26quot%3B)%20to%20describe%20how%20much%20they%20miss%20things%20from%20when%20they%20were%20younger.%20The%20topics%20are%20things%20like%20%26quot%3Bfamily%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bheroes%20or%20heroines%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bthings%20you%20did%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Btoys%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bholidays%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bthe%20way%20society%20was%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Byour%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bnot%20knowing%20sad%20or%20evil%20things.%26quot%3B%20Finally%2C%20the%20respondents%20were%20asked%2C%20as%20a%20means%20of%20confirmation%2C%20how%20lonely%20they%20felt%20on%20a%20scale%20of%201%20to%205.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20here's%20the%20trick.%20That%20first%20questionnaire%2C%20the%20loneliness%20one%2C%20was%20faked.%20The%20researchers%20pulled%20questions%20from%20the%20UCLA%20test%20but%20rigged%20it%20by%20tweaking%20the%20questions.%20Then%20they%20didn't%20actually%20score%20it%2C%20but%20randomized%20whether%20they%20told%20the%20person%20they%20had%20a%20high%20degree%20of%20loneliness%20(in%20the%2062nd%20percentile%20of%20loneliness)%20or%20a%20low%20degree%20of%20loneliness%20(in%20the%2012th%20percentile%20of%20loneliness).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EIf%20the%20key%20driver%20of%20reboots%20is%20nostalgia%20%E2%80%94%20then%20the%20key%20driver%20of%20nostalgia%20is%20loneliness.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20goal%20wasn't%20actually%20to%20determine%20how%20lonely%20they%20were.%20It%20was%20to%20prime%20them%2C%20to%20make%20them%20think%20either%20that%20they%20were%20more%20lonely%20than%20the%20typical%20person%20or%20less%20lonely%20than%20average.%20It%20worked.%20That%20confirmation%2C%20asking%20them%20how%20lonely%20they%20felt.%20The%20group%20primed%20to%20feel%20less%20lonely%20%E2%80%94%20the%20people%20who%20were%20told%20they%20had%20low%20loneliness%20after%20the%20fake%20first%20test%20%E2%80%94%20reported%20an%20average%20loneliness%20of%201.3%2C%20whereas%20the%20group%20primed%20to%20believe%20they%20had%20high%20loneliness%20reported%20an%20average%20of%202.9%20out%20of%205.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20results%20were%20consistent%20with%20a%20causal%20relationship%20between%20loneliness%20and%20nostalgia.%20They%20found%20that%20the%20group%20that%20was%20told%20they%20were%20lonelier%20scored%20higher%20on%20the%20nostalgia%20index%20(an%20average%20score%20of%203.01)%20than%20the%20group%20who%20believed%20they%20were%20less%20lonely%20(an%20average%20of%202.56).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ratings%20of%20nostalgia%20for%20%26quot%3Bmy%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bthe%20way%20people%20were%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bhaving%20someone%20to%20depend%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bnot%20having%20to%20worry%26quot%3B%20were%20significantly%20higher%20statistically%20among%20those%20primed%20for%20loneliness%20compared%20with%20those%20who%20were%20not.%20It%20corroborated%20the%20idea%20that%20there's%20a%20fundamental%20link%20between%20feelings%20of%20being%20alone%20and%20the%20psychological%20emergence%20of%20nostalgia.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20loneliness%20epidemic%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20rise%20of%20nostalgia%20in%20media%20is%20mostly%20anecdotal%2C%20there's%20repeated%20evidence%20that%20people%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20younger%20people%20%E2%80%94%20are%20more%20lonely%20than%20before%2C%20and%20that%20things%20like%20social%20media%20can%20exacerbate%20those%20feelings%20of%20loneliness.%20American%20health%20insurer%20Cigna%20has%20conducted%20a%20large%20loneliness%20survey%20since%202018%2C%20with%20over%20ten%20thousand%20respondents%20in%20the%20sample%20annually.%20In%202020%2C%2061%25%20of%20those%20surveyed%20were%20lonely%2C%20up%207%20percentage%20points%20since%20the%20survey%20was%20first%20conducted%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETime%20and%20again%2C%20polling%20illustrates%20that%20Americans%20of%20all%20ages%20are%20experiencing%20serious%20loneliness%2C%20which%20was%20exacerbated%20significantly%20by%20a%20pandemic.%20A%20September%202022%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20survey%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2022%2F12%2F12%2Fat-least-four-in-ten-u-s-adults-have-faced-high-levels-of-psychological-distress-during-covid-19-pandemic%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E41%25%20of%20respondents%3C%2Fa%3E%20felt%20lonely%20in%20at%20least%20one%20or%20two%20of%20the%20past%20seven%20days.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20the%20loneliness%20is%20extreme%3A%20A%20Pew%20Research%20survey%20from%20this%20summer%20found%20that%208%25%20of%20Americans%20said%20they%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F10%2F12%2Fwhat-does-friendship-look-like-in-america%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eno%20close%20friends%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20Gallup%20survey%20from%20February%202023%20asked%20if%20respondents%20experienced%20loneliness%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20day%20yesterday%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F473057%2Floneliness-subsides-pandemic-high.aspx%23%3A~%3Atext%3DDespite%2520the%2520decrease%252C%2520the%252017%2CHealth%2520and%2520Well%252DBeing%2520Index.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E17%25%20said%20yes%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20down%20from%20the%20pandemic%20high%20of%2025%25%2C%20but%20still%20means%20that%20one%20in%20six%20people%20felt%20lonely%20yesterday.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20expectation%20might%20be%20that%20elderly%20people%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20feel%20lonely%2C%20the%20opposite%20is%20true%3A%20It%20was%20people%20aged%2018%20to%2029%20with%20the%20highest%20percentages%20of%20loneliness%2C%20hitting%2024%25%20compared%20to%20just%2013%25%20among%20those%2065%20and%20up.%20It's%20young%20people%20%E2%80%94%20the%20primary%20demographic%20targeted%20for%20mainstream%20pop%20culture%20%E2%80%94%20who%20are%20feeling%20lonely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20have%20not%20always%20been%20this%20way.%20An%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.psypost.org%2F2022%2F01%2Fmassive-meta-analysis-finds-loneliness-has-increased-in-emerging-adults-in-the-last-43-years-62377%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%20of%20345%20studies%20of%20loneliness%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20between%201976%20and%202019%20that%20covered%20124%2C855%20participants%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2018%20and%2029%20found%20that%20there%20was%20a%20steady%20increase%20in%20reported%20levels%20of%20loneliness%20over%20time%20through%20about%202012%2C%20at%20which%20point%20the%20increase%20leveled%20off%20and%20has%20held%20steady.%20This%20would%20appear%20to%20align%20with%20the%20mainstream%20introduction%20of%20smartphones%2C%20certainly%2C%20but%20it%20also%20aligns%20with%20another%20thing%3A%20the%20utter%20dominance%20of%20reboot%20and%20nostalgia-based%20entertainment.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECash%20cows%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENostalgia-driven%20media%20has%20become%20a%20behemoth.%20The%20first%20legacy%20reboots%20%E2%80%94%20films%20that%20attempted%20to%20introduce%20new%20characters%20following%20in%20the%20footsteps%20of%20the%20main%20characters%20of%20films%20produced%20a%20generation%20ago%20%E2%80%94%20truly%20kicked%20off%20with%20%26quot%3BIndiana%20Jones%20and%20the%20Kingdom%20of%20the%20Crystal%20Skull%26quot%3B%20in%202008%2C%20followed%20by%20%26quot%3BTRON%3A%20Legacy%26quot%3B%20in%202010.%20The%20levee%20quickly%20broke%2C%20and%20by%202015%2C%20%26quot%3BJurassic%20World%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BTerminator%20Genisys%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BStar%20Wars%3A%20The%20Force%20Awakens%26quot%3B%20were%20throwing%20gasoline%20on%20that%20fire.%20Since%20then%2C%20standalone%20films%20like%20%26quot%3BIndependence%20Day%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BTrainspotting%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BBlade%20Runner%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BThe%20Incredibles%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BThe%20Shining%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BGhostbusters%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BComing%20to%20America%26quot%3B%20have%20all%20seen%20a%20legacy%20sequel%20cash-in%20attempt.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221356%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Multi-bonded%20interconnected%20franchise%20data%20visualization%20for%20Marvel%20films%20and%20The%20Fast%20and%20The%20Furious%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536cbe70487ff031cac0a02%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22878%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EHeather%20Jones%20(art)%2C%20Walt%20Hickey%20(data)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20this%20business%20strategy%20works.%20The%20top%20movie%20this%20year%20is%20about%20a%20childhood%20toy%2C%20the%20top%20three%20movies%20of%202022%20worldwide%20were%20%26quot%3BTop%20Gun%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BAvatar%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quo