man-being%2Farticleshow%2F104668429.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NASA%20Unable%20To%20Remove%20Remaining%20Asteroid%20Sample%20From%20Container%2C%20Says...%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20a%20NASA%20capsule%20landed%20in%20the%20desert%20in%20the%20US%20state%20of%20Utah%2C%20carrying%20to%20Earth%20the%20largest%20asteroid%20samples%20ever%20collected.%20On%20October%2011%2C%C2%A0NASA%20gave%20the%20world%20its%20first%20look%20at%20the%20asteroid%20Bennu%20sample%2C%C2%A0something%20scientists%20hope%20will%20yield%20clues%20about%20the%20earliest%20days%20of%20our%20solar%20system%20and%20perhaps%20the%20origins%20of%20life%20itself.%C2%A0%20So%20far%2C%20the%20team%C2%A0has%20removed%20and%20collected%202.48%20ounces%20(70.3%20grams)%20of%20rocks%20and%20dust%20from%20the%20sampler%20hardware.%20According%20to%20NASA%2C%20the%20samples%20exceed%20the%20mission's%20goal%20of%20collecting%2060%20grams%20of%20debris%20from%20the%20asteroid.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20more%20samples%20to%20collect%2C%20however%2C%20the%C2%A0teams%20at%20NASA's%20Johnson%20Space%20Center%20(JSC)%20are%20now%20struggling%20to%20open%20the%20canister.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20week%2C%20the%20team%20for%20the%20OSIRIS-REx%20mission%20has%20had%20a%20hard%20time%20opening%20the%20TAGSAM%20head%2C%20which%20contained%20the%20bulk%20of%20the%20rocks%20and%20dust%20collected%20by%20the%20spacecraft%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E''After%20multiple%20attempts%20at%20removal%2C%20the%20team%20discovered%20two%20of%20the%2035%20fasteners%20on%20the%20TAGSAM%20head%20could%20not%20be%20removed%20with%20the%20current%20tools%20approved%20for%20use%20in%20the%20OSIRIS-REx%20glovebox.%20The%20team%20has%20been%20working%20to%20develop%20and%20implement%20new%20approaches%20to%20extract%20the%20material%20inside%20the%20head%20while%20continuing%20to%20keep%20the%20sample%20safe%20and%20pristine%2C''%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblogs.nasa.gov%2Fosiris-rex%2F2023%2F10%2F20%2Fnasas-osiris-rex-achieves-sample-mass-milestone%2F%5C%22%3ENASA%20wrote%20in%20a%20blog%20post.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20will%20now%C2%A0spend%20the%20next%20few%20weeks%20developing%20and%20practicing%20a%20new%20procedure%20to%20remove%20the%20remaining%20asteroid%20sample%20from%20the%20TAGSAM%20sampler%20head%20while%20simultaneously%20processing%20the%20material%20that%20was%20collected%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E''All%20curation%20work%20on%20the%20sample%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20TAGSAM%20head%20%E2%80%93%20is%20performed%20in%20a%20specialized%20glovebox%20under%20a%20flow%20of%20nitrogen%20to%20keep%20it%20from%20being%20exposed%20to%20Earth's%20atmosphere%2C%20preserving%20the%20sample's%20pristine%20state%20for%20subsequent%20scientific%20analysis.%20The%20tools%20for%20any%20proposed%20solution%20to%20extract%20the%20remaining%20material%20from%20the%20head%20must%20be%20able%20to%20fit%20inside%20the%20glovebox%20and%20not%20compromise%20the%20scientific%20integrity%20of%20the%20collection%2C%20and%20any%20procedures%20must%20be%20consistent%20with%20the%20clean%20room's%20standards%2C''%20NASA%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOSIRIS-REx%20wasn't%20the%20first%20mission%20to%20rendezvous%20with%20an%20asteroid%20and%20bring%20back%20samples%20for%20study%20--%20Japan%20succeeded%20in%20the%20feat%20twice%2C%20returning%20bits%20of%20space%20pebbles%20in%202010%20and%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20NASA%20chose%20to%20sample%20Bennu%20because%20it%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20rich%20in%20organic%20compounds.%20Scientists%20think%20similar%20asteroids%20could%20have%20delivered%20organic%20building%20blocks%20to%20Earth%20along%20with%20water%20through%20collisions%20billions%20of%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20has%20no%20chance%20of%20hitting%20Earth%20through%20the%20mid%202100s%2C%20the%20chances%20rise%20to%20around%201%20in%201750%20between%20then%20and%20the%20year%202300%2C%20NASA%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698127980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fkln9hbpg_-asteroid-bennu-_625x300_24_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasa-unable-to-remove-remaining-asteroid-sample-from-container-working-on-new-ways-4508991%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20are%20more%20samples%20to%20collect%2C%20however%2C%20the%20teams%20at%20NASA's%20Johnson%20Space%20Center%20(JSC)%20are%20now%20struggling%20to%20open%20the%20canister.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasa-unable-to-remove-remaining-asteroid-sample-from-container-working-on-new-ways-4508991%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasa-unable-to-remove-remaining-asteroid-sample-from-container-working-on-new-ways-4508991%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasa-unable-to-remove-remaining-asteroid-sample-from-container-working-on-new-ways-4508991%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Angad%20pays%20tribute%20to%20dad%20Bishan%20Singh%20Bedi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698127803000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104667581%2Cimgsize-107278.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fbishan-singh-bedi-passes-away-angad-bedi-and-family-in-shock-and-overcome-with-grief-say-he-bowled-us-over-with-the-ultimate-spin-ball%2Farticleshow%2F104667119.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104667119.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EAngad%20Bedi%2C%20son%20of%20legendary%20cricketer%20Bishan%20Singh%20Bedi%2C%20penned%20a%2