0has%20come%20to%20be%20from%20the%2018th%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECould%20you%20tell%20us%20about%20your%20use%20of%20multilingual%20sources%20and%20how%20you%20worked%20with%20original%20texts%20and%20translations%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDouglas%20Ober%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20One%20of%20the%20major%20challenges%20to%20the%20study%20of%20Buddhism%20during%20this%20period%20is%20that%20Buddhist%20works%20and%2For%20references%20to%20Buddhism%20were%20produced%20in%20a%20wide%20array%20of%20languages%20and%20scripts.%20We%E2%80%99re%20accustomed%20to%20thinking%20about%20South%20Asian%20Buddhism%20as%20something%20that%20is%20tied%20to%20so-called%20canonical%20languages%20like%20Pali%20and%20Sanskrit%2C%20but%20if%20we%20only%20focus%20on%20these%2C%20we%20risk%20losing%20sight%20of%20the%20bigger%20picture.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOnce%20I%20realised%20that%20I%20wanted%20to%20craft%20a%20pan-Indian%20and%20even%20global%20narrative%20and%20understand%20how%20ideas%20connected%20across%20regions%2C%20I%20chose%20to%20read%20widely%20rather%20than%20focus%20on%20just%20a%20few%20select%20texts%20or%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMy%20own%20Asian%20language%20training%20was%20in%20Hindi%2C%20Tibetan%2C%20Sanskrit%20and%20Pali%20%E2%80%93%20so%20that%20was%20my%20base.%20I%20also%20drew%20on%20numerous%20translations%20from%20other%20languages%20into%20English%2C%20Hindi%20and%20French.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20the%20book%20drew%20on%20primary%20and%20secondary%20sources%20that%20had%20also%20been%20originally%20composed%20in%20Bengali%2C%20Burmese%2C%20French%2C%20Japanese%2C%20Malayalam%2C%20Marathi%2C%20Nepali%2C%20Persian%2C%20Russian%2C%20Tamil%2C%20Telugu%20and%20Urdu.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EObviously%2C%20I%20am%20standing%20on%20the%20shoulders%20of%20those%20who%20made%20those%20sources%20available%20to%20me%20%E2%80%93%20mostly%20in%20previously%20published%20works%20but%20also%20in%20archives%20and%20in%20a%20few%20cases%2C%20colleagues%20and%20friends%20who%20provided%20direct%20translations%20or%20summaries%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Today%2C%20the%20scholarship%20on%20modern%20Indian%20Buddhism%20focuses%20on%20conditions%20in%20Anglo-America%20and%20its%20various%20pathologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20you%20have%20charted%20a%20new%20direction.%20You%20examine%20what%20%E2%80%98modern%E2%80%99%20Buddhism%20did%20for%2C%20and%20meant%20to%20Indian%20scholars%20of%20religion%2C%20amateur%20historians%20%E2%80%93%20those%20who%20took%20%3Cem%3Edeeksha%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20those%20from%20within%20existing%20and%20active%20Buddhist%20communities%2C%20and%20how%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20these%20diverse%20individuals%20and%20groups%20helped%20bring%20modern%20Buddhism%20into%20existence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWas%20there%20a%20specific%20text%20or%20argument%20that%20you%20identified%20which%20set%20you%20off%20on%20this%20course%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Frethinking-manuscript-practices-in-india%5C%22%3ERethinking%20India%E2%80%99s%20Manuscript%20Practices%20as%20Official%20Policy%20Undervalues%20Its%20Rich%20Heritage%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20terms%20of%20secondary%20scholarship%2C%20I%20was%20greatly%20influenced%20by%20the%20turn%20to%20trans-regional%20networks%20and%20%E2%80%98translocative%20flows%E2%80%99%20by%20scholars%20like%20Thomas%20Tweed%2C%20Anne%20Blackburn%2C%20Richard%20Jaffe%2C%20Sanjay%20Subramanyam%20and%20Nile%20Green.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20before%20starting%20the%20research%2C%20I%20had%20been%20inspired%20by%20the%20Tibetan-language%20memoir%20of%20the%20Tibetan%20Buddhist%20savant%2C%20Gendun%20Chopel%2C%20who%20travelled%20to%20India%20from%20Tibet%20in%20the%201930s%20and%20mingled%20with%20many%20of%20Asia%E2%80%99s%20and%20Europe%E2%80%99s%20leading%20Buddhist%20figures%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChopel%20led%20me%20to%20the%20Marxist%20scholar%20and%20sometimes%20Buddhist%20monk%2C%20Rahul%20Sankrityayan.%20As%20my%20research%20really%20began%20to%20unfold%2C%20I%20read%20the%20entirety%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FMeri_Jeevan_Yatra%5C%22%3ERahul%20Sankrityayan%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EMeri%20Jivan%20Yatra%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20used%20it%20to%20draw%20up%20a%20map%20of%20where%20Buddhism%20circulated%20during%20this%20period%20and%20how%20it%20shaped%20such%20a%20diverse%20social%20landscape.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20Meera%20Kosambi%20translated%20(from%20Marathi%20into%20English)%20many%20of%20the%20writings%20of%20her%20grandfather%2C%20Dharmanand%20Kosambi%20%E2%80%93%20the%20great%20Pali%20scholar%20and%20also%20sometimes%20Buddhist%20monk%20%E2%80%93%20I%20realised%20that%20there%20were%20all%20kinds%20of%20intellectual%2C%20social%20and%20political%20patterns%20that%20tied%20these%20histories%20together.%20I%20then%20set%20off%20to%20explore%20them%2C%20and%20as%20I%20did%2C%20a%20kind%20of%20map%20of%20Buddhism%20in%20modern%20Asia%20began%20to%20reveal%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20One%20of%20the%20things%20that%20fascinated%20me%20about%20your%20approach%20was%20your%20sense%20of%20wonder%20%E2%80%93%20at%20what%20workers%20in%20Buddhist%20sites%2C%20digging%20up%20or%20uncovering%20ruins%2C%20possibly%20made%20of%20what%20they%20were%20doing%2C%20and%20of%20local%20lore%20that%20might%20have%20engaged%20their%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fiyodhee-thass-pandithar-a-pioneer-in-dalit-history-and-literature%5C%22%3ETamil%20scholar%20Stalin%20Rajangam%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20noted%20that%20in%20almost%20all%20his%20wanderings%20through%20Jaina%20and%20Buddhist%20sites%20in%20the%20Tamil%20countryside%2C%20he%20has%20come%20across%20local%20histories%20which%20exist%20as%20forms%20of%20recall.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20since%20questioned%20the%20truth%20claims%20of%20sources%3A%20inscriptions%2C%20literature%2C%20local%20lore%2C%20diffuse%20public%20memory%20%E2%80%A6%20what%20they%20tell%20us%20or%20fail%20to%20tell%20us%20about%20Jaina%20and%20Buddhist%20presence%20in%20these%20landscapes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20context%2C%20your%20ruminations%20about%20the%20workers%20and%20their%20sense%20of%20the%20past%20pushes%20us%20to%20reflect%20on%20our%20own%20textual%20and%20other%20labour.%20What%20made%20you%20want%20to%20know%20more%20about%20those%20who%20helped%20%E2%80%98recover%E2%80%99%20Buddhist%20monuments%2C%20whose%20labour%20literally%20marks%20the%20%E2%80%98presence%E2%80%99%20of%20Buddhism%20in%20modern%20India%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fraja-sivaprasad-and-the-lost-history-of-buddhism%5C%22%3ERaja%20Sivaprasad%20and%20the%20Lost%20History%20of%20Buddhism%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Truth%20be%20told%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20sure%20what%20led%20me%20to%20ask%20these%20kinds%20of%20questions.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20just%20a%20curious%20person%20and%20want%20to%20better%20understand%20what%20people%20think%20and%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20I%20think%20some%20of%20this%20may%20have%20stemmed%20from%20my%20early%20training%20in%20religious%20studies%2C%20which%20was%20largely%20driven%20by%20anthropological%20approaches%20that%20cast%20a%20more%20critical%20eye%20on%20the%20role%20that%20text%20and%20doctrine%20played%20in%20everyday%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETwo%20of%20my%20early%20mentors%20(both%20of%20whom%20have%20now%20sadly%20passed)%2C%20Kyoko%20Tokuno%20(a%20historian%20of%20Chinese%20Buddhism)%20and%20Charles%20Keyes%20(an%20anthropologist%20of%20Theravada%20Buddhism)%2C%20always%20encouraged%20me%20to%20think%20beyond%20the%20text%20and%20question%20the%20relationship%20between%20the%20lived%20and%20textual%20tradition.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20I%20think%20almost%20each%20of%20your%20chapters%20contains%20themes%20that%20can%20fill%20an%20entire%20a%20book%2C%20some%20are%20particularly%20significant%3A%20I%20was%20wondering%20if%20you%20could%20tell%20us%20a%20little%20more%20about%20each%20of%20these.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETake%20the%20chapter%20on%20the%20Hinduising%20of%20Buddhism%3A%20here%2C%20you%20have%20meticulously%20dealt%20with%20the%20role%20played%20by%20individuals%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FJugal_Kishore_Birla%5C%22%3EJugal%20Kishore%20Birla%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Given%20how%20the%20Buddha%20and%20Buddhism%20have%20shadowed%20philosophical%20traditions%20antithetical%20to%20what%20they%20stood%20for%2C%20do%20you%20see%20this%20manner%20of%20Hinduising%20as%20a%20moment%20in%20this%20long%20history%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOr%20did%20it%20have%20to%20do%20as%20much%20with%20an%20anti-colonial%20politics%2C%20which%20sought%20to%20%E2%80%98recover%E2%80%99%20a%20worthy%20golden%20age%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20think%20it%20has%20to%20do%20with%20both.%20There%20is%20a%20real%20resonance%20between%20the%20medieval%20appropriation%20of%20the%20Buddha%20via%20the%20Vishnu%20avatar%20and%20the%20modern%20Hindu%20appropriation%20of%20the%20Buddha%20as%20a%20great%20Hindu%20social%20reformer.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBoth%20developments%20emerged%20out%20of%20long-standing%20debates%20between%20Brahmins%20and%20Buddhists%2C%20as%20well%20as%20local%20political%20conditions%2C%20and%20real%20and%20imagined%20threats.%20So%2C%20there%20is%20real%20continuity%20here%20and%20the%20colonial-era%20Indians%20who%20worked%20to%20Brahmanise%20Buddhism%20were%20well%20aware%20of%20this%20longer%20history%20and%20looked%20to%20it%20for%20inspiration%20and%20guidance.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fconversion-hinduism-buddhism-modi%5C%22%3EAmidst%20%E2%80%98Conversion%E2%80%99%20Brouhaha%2C%20PM%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20Words%20in%20Bali%20Cement%20a%20Truth%20About%20Hinduism%E2%80%99s%20Spread%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20distinctive%20differences%2C%20which%20as%20you%20mention%2C%20were%20tied%20to%20anti-colonial%20politics%2C%20the%20nationalist%20fetish%20for%20a%20glorious%20past%20and%20%5Bthe%5D%20question%20of%20how%20a%20Hindu%20nation%20would%20fit%20into%20a%20modern%20Asian%20world%20that%20was%20increasingly%20imagined%20as%20Buddhist.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20think%20these%20external%20pressures%20of%20anti-colonialism%20and%20pan-Asianism%2C%20along%20with%20the%20growing%20resonance%20that%20Buddhism%20held%20among%20anti-caste%20leaders%20in%20India%2C%20created%20a%20sense%20of%20urgency%20that%20this%20so-called%20Buddhist%20revival%20needed%20to%20be%20addressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Within%20South%20Asia%2C%20there%20were%20different%20approaches%20at%20making%20Buddhism%20relevant%20and%20claiming%20it%20as%20worthwhile%20tradition.%20Like%20you%20write%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20attend%20to%20vernacular%20articulations%20of%20Buddhism%20to%20get%20a%20sense%20of%20its%20continued%20presence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHow%20might%20one%20think%20of%20Buddhism%20in%20the%20modern%20period%20then%3F%20Are%20these%20different%20ways%20of%20thinking%20about%20Buddhism%20variations%20on%20a%20set%20of%20common%20themes%3F%20Or%20do%20they%20signify%20distinctive%20approaches%2C%20shaped%20by%20specific%20histories%20and%20geographies%3F%20If%20so%2C%20what%20renders%20these%20projects%20%E2%80%98equally%E2%80%99%20modern%3F%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Local%20histories%20and%20their%20interactions%20with%20other%20cultural%20and%20religious%20traditions%20have%20always%20played%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20shaping%20the%20way%20Buddhism%20is%20practiced%20and%20understood.%20Yet%20despite%20the%20diversity%20of%20approaches%2C%20many%20of%20these%20adaptations%20of%20Buddhism%20retain%20core%20Buddhist%20principles%20and%20practices%2C%20and%20the%20ethical%20and%20philosophical%20teachings%20are%20preserved%2C%20albeit%20in%20different%20forms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20tension%20here%2C%20of%20course.%20Who%20is%20to%20say%20what%20the%20%E2%80%98essence%E2%80%99%20is%3F%20At%20what%20point%20has%20something%20deviated%20too%20far%20from%20those%20essential%20principles%20and%20practices%3F%20It%20is%20in%20those%20tensions%20that%20we%20can%20often%20best%20understand%20what%20constitutes%20a%20Buddhist%20tradition.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20of%20modernity%20is%20exceedingly%20complex%20but%20in%20its%20simplest%20formation%2C%20I%E2%80%99d%20argue%20that%20what%20renders%20these%20traditions%20modern%20is%20their%20adaptation%20to%20contemporary%20circumstances%20and%20their%20continued%20connections%20to%20the%20past.%20That%20adaptability%20is%20the%20hallmark%20of%20Buddhist%20history%2C%20of%20the%20Buddha%E2%80%99s%20skilful%20means%20or%20method%20(%3Cem%3Eupaya%3C%2Fem%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20From%20archival%20and%20other%20sources%20you%20have%20assembled%2C%20it%20is%20evident%20that%20the%20concern%20with%20the%20past%2C%20with%20a%20putative%20golden%20age%2C%20had%20not%20only%20to%20do%20with%20%E2%80%98the%20wonder%20that%20was%20India%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20with%20a%20time%20that%20resonated%20with%20modern%20values%2C%20especially%20of%20equality%2C%20justice%20and%20fraternity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYour%20book%20asks%20us%20to%20rethink%20the%20historiographical%20concerns%20of%20late%20colonial%20India.%20So%2C%20the%20debates%20of%20the%20time%20did%20not%20only%C2%A0have%20to%20do%20with%20civilisational%20%E2%80%98differences%E2%80%99%20(Aryan%20vs.%20Dravidian%3B%20%3Cem%3Emulnivasi%3C%2Fem%3E%20vs.%20settlers)%3B%20or%20authentic%20and%20alien%20rule%20(%E2%80%98Hindu%E2%80%99%20India%20vs%20%E2%80%98Muslim%E2%80%99%20India).%20They%20also%20had%20to%20do%20with%20philosophical%20traditions%20that%20were%20claimed%20as%20their%20own%20by%20a%20host%20of%20anti-caste%20radicals.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fhow-hindutva-historiography-is-rooted-in-the-colonial-view-of-indian-history%5C%22%3EHow%20Hindutva%20Historiography%20is%20Rooted%20in%20the%20Colonial%20View%20of%20Indian%20History%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20was%20reading%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbrill.com%2Fview%2Fjournals%2Fsaih%2Faop%2Farticle-10.1163-25425552-12340042%2Farticle-10.1163-25425552-12340042.xml%3Flanguage%3Den%5C%22%3EEric%20Gurevitch%E2%80%99s%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20Jaina%20debates%20on%20caste%20in%20the%20western%20Chalukyan%20courts%20and%20it%20is%20evident%20that%20the%20%3Cem%3Esramana%3C%2Fem%3E%20traditions%20had%20things%20to%20say%20which%20modern%20anti-caste%20radicals%20found%20attractive.%20In%20this%20sense%2C%20any%20study%20of%20modern%20Indian%20thought%20must%20necessarily%20include%20Iyothee%20Thass%2C%20Bodhanand%2C%20Dharmanand%20Kosambi%E2%80%A6%20would%20you%20like%20to%20reflect%20on%20this%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20You%E2%80%99re%20absolutely%20right%3A%20whether%20it%20was%20a%20reimagining%20of%20the%20Buddha%20as%20a%20champion%20of%20social%20justice%20or%20an%20exploration%20of%20ancient%20texts%20for%20egalitarian%20ideas%2C%20there%20was%20a%20strong%20connection%20between%20the%20past%20and%20the%20ideals%20of%20the%20present.%20The%20%3Cem%3Esramana%3C%2Fem%3E%20traditions%20often%20had%20a%20history%20of%20challenging%20established%20hierarchies.%20Modern%20leaders%20drew%20on%20them%20to%20advocate%20for%20social%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20societies%20have%20their%20fracture%20lines%2C%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20questions%20of%20foreign%20rule%2C%20or%20settlers%20versus%20natives%2C%20civilisational%20differences%20and%20so%20on%2C%20but%20I%20think%20the%20works%20of%20towering%20intellectuals%20like%20Thass%2C%20Kosambi%20and%20others%20make%20clear%20that%20these%20were%20also%20questions%20deeply%20intertwined%20with%20values%20of%20equality%2C%20justice%20and%20fraternity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20rich%20philosophical%20heritage%20resonates%20with%20these%20values%20and%20if%20we%20want%20to%20better%20understand%20not%20only%20the%20subcontinent%E2%80%99s%20history%20but%20also%20the%20historiographical%20concerns%20of%20late%20colonial%20India%2C%20we%20must%20take%20them%20seriously.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20chapter%20on%20Buddhism%20and%20the%20socialist%20imagination%20is%20rich%2C%20and%20I%20was%20wondering%20what%20you%20think%20of%20this%20in%20the%20context%20of%20other%20such%20efforts%20that%20link%20labour%2C%20the%20working%20class%20and%20Buddhism%3A%20for%20instance%20Laurence%20Cox%E2%80%99s%20(with%20Alicia%20Turner%20and%20Brian%20Bocking)%20book%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faeon.co%2Fessays%2Fu-dhammaloka-the-irish-buddhist-monk-who-faced-down-imperialism%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Irish%20Buddhist%3A%20the%20Forgotten%20Monk%20who%20Faced%20Down%20the%20British%20Empire%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20am%20a%20huge%20admirer%20of%20Laurence%20Cox%E2%80%99s%20scholarship%20and%20I%20remain%20greatly%20inspired%20by%20the%20model%20of%20%E2%80%9Cplebeian%20cosmopolitanism%E2%80%9D%20that%20Cox%2C%20Turner%20and%20Bocking%20put%20forth%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Irish%20Buddhist%3C%2Fem%3E.%20I%20think%20the%20entire%20U%20Dhammaloka%20project%20(out%20of%20which%20it%20emerged)%20has%20opened%20so%20many%20new%20avenues%20for%20understanding%20Buddhism%E2%80%99s%2020th%20century%20connections%20to%20the%20working%20classes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20combined%20with%20the%20insights%20provided%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.orientblackswan.com%2Fdetails%3Fid%3D9788125037019%5C%22%3EHarald%20Fischer-Tin%C3%A9%E2%80%99s%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20race%2C%20class%20and%20white%20subalternity%20in%20colonial%20India%2C%20I%20think%20an%20entirely%20new%20sub-field%20could%20be%20created.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJust%20consider%20the%20Irish%20Buddhist%20radicals%20who%20worked%20with%20Tamil%20Buddhist%20migrants%20and%20labourers%20in%20early%2020th-century%20India%20in%20places%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbuddhistcentrekgf.com%2F%5C%22%3EKolar%20Gold%20Fields%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There%20is%20so%20little%20we%20know%20about%20these%20connections%20%E2%80%A6%20but%20it%20has%20all%20the%20makings%20of%20an%20Amitav%20Ghosh%20novel!%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Lastly%3A%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20Buddhist%20diplomacy%20gave%20an%20entirely%20new%20twist%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epw.in%2Fjournal%2F2016%2F1%2Fperspectives%2Fbrief-history-panchsheel.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98panchsheel%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20non-aligned%20movement%2C%20and%20this%20contrasts%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Fpageturner%2Fcentral-railways-sent-special-train-museum-gave-statue-for-ambedkars-buddhism-conversion%2F1801057%2F%5C%22%3EAmbedkar%E2%80%99s%20world-transforming%20project%20of%20taking%20deeksha%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20nearly%20half%20a%20million%20followers.%20The%20former%20seems%20an%20exercise%20in%20anti-colonial%20worldmaking%20and%20diplomacy%2C%20and%20the%20latter%20stakes%20claims%20on%20a%20utopia%20and%20on%20reconstructing%20the%20world.%20Could%20you%20comment%20on%20this%20contrast%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20think%20you%20are%20right%3A%20these%20are%20two%20different%20approaches%20at%20addressing%20the%20challenges%20in%20post-colonial%20India%20and%20