e%20combat%20aircraft%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20officials%20say%20pilots%20will%20be%20able%20control%20to%20conduct%20a%20number%20of%20missions%20that%20extend%20their%20range%20and%20reduce%20their%20workload.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Navy%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnavy-aircraft-carriers-may-soon-fight-alongside-drone-ships-aircraft-2022-4%5C%22%3Eflying%20small%20drones%20from%20its%20ships%20for%20years%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20aircraft%2C%20like%20the%20MQ-8B%20and%20MQ-8C%20unmanned%20helicopters%2C%20mainly%20operate%20from%20frigates%20and%20littoral%20combat%20ships%20and%20conduct%20intelligence%2C%20surveillance%2C%20and%20reconnaissance%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Navy%20littoral%20combat%20ship%20USS%20Tulsa%20MQ-8B%20Fire%20Scout%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F624686ce2d38730018f4dc7a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221429%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESailors%20with%20an%20MQ-8B%20aboard%20littoral%20combat%20ship%20USS%20Tulsa%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean%20in%20April%202021.%3Cp%3EUS%20NavyMCS2%20Colby%20A.%20Mothershead%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Navy%20is%20also%20developing%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-china-developing-new-aerial-refueling-tankers-to-extend-range-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20MQ-25%20Stingray%20aerial-refueling%20drone%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20its%20aircraft%20carriers.%20In%20addition%20to%20freeing%20up%20the%20F%2FA-18%20fighter%20jets%20that%20currently%20perform%20carrier-borne%20aerial-refueling%20missions%2C%20the%20MQ-25%20could%20eventually%20take%20on%20other%20roles%2C%20like%20intelligence-gathering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Stingray%2C%20which%20is%20scheduled%20to%20deploy%20in%202026%2C%20will%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-making-plans-to-load-aircraft-carriers-with-drones-2022-10%5C%22%3Ethe%20first%20purpose-built%20carrier-based%20drone%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20it%20won't%20be%20the%20last.%20The%20US%20Navy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-making-plans-to-load-aircraft-carriers-with-drones-2022-10%5C%22%3Eaims%20for%2060%25%20of%20its%20carrier%20wing%20fleet%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20unmanned%20by%202045.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncorporating%20unmanned%20aircraft%20into%20carrier%20operations%20alongside%20manned%20planes%20and%20helicopters%20will%20be%20challenging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNaval%20aviation%20is%20an%20exacting%20job%20with%20little%20to%20no%20margin%20for%20error%2C%20particularly%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20carrier%20landings%2C%26quot%3B%20Alex%20Hollings%2C%20an%20aviation%20expert%20and%20journalist%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20the%20landing%20deck%20sometimes%20pitching%20by%20as%20much%20as%2030%20feet%20with%20the%20waves%2C%20carrier%20landings%20are%20often%20hard%20enough%20to%20seriously%20damage%20ordinary%20aircraft%2C%20and%20things%20only%20get%20worse%20at%20night%20or%20in%20poor%20weather%2C%26quot%3B%20Hollings%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20a%20study%20of%20Navy%20pilots%20during%20the%20Vietnam%20War%20showed%20their%20heart%20rates%20were%20more%20elevated%20just%20before%20night%20landings%20on%20a%20carrier%20than%20when%20trying%20to%20shake%20incoming%20surface-to-air%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22MQ-25%20Navy%20aircraft%20carrier%20USS%20George%20H.W.%20Bush%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F624683c17bf4e60019369d37%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221428%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20MQ-25%20on%20the%20flight%20deck%20of%20the%20aircraft%20carrier%20USS%20George%20H.W.%20Bush%20in%20December%202021.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%2FMCS3%20Brandon%20Roberson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20t