ld-middle-east-67201107.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67201107.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China%20could%20strike%20far%20more%20than%20just%20flattops%20with%20its%20growing%20arsenal%20of%20'carrier-killer'%20missiles%2C%20defense%20expert%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Military%20vehicles%20carrying%20DF-26%20ballistic%20missiles%2C%20drive%20past%20the%20Tiananmen%20Gate%20during%20a%20military%20parade%20to%20mark%20the%2070th%20anniversary%20of%20the%20end%20of%20World%20War%20Two%20on%20September%203%2C%202015%2C%20in%20Beijing%2C%20China.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536cd300487ff031cac0d0f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMilitary%20vehicles%20carrying%20DF-26%20ballistic%20missiles%2C%20drive%20past%20the%20Tiananmen%20Gate%20during%20a%20military%20parade%20to%20mark%20the%2070th%20anniversary%20of%20the%20end%20of%20World%20War%20Two%20on%20September%203%2C%202015%2C%20in%20Beijing%2C%20China.%3Cp%3EAndy%20Wong%20-%20Pool%20%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20Department%20of%20Defense%20published%20its%20annual%20China%20Military%20Power%20Report%20last%20week.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EIn%20the%20update%2C%20the%20Pentagon%20assesses%20China%20bolstered%20its%20missile%20stockpiles%2C%20specifically%20its%20DF-26%20supply.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EIf%20China%20has%20more%20DF-26s%2C%20called%20%26quot%3Bcarrier%20killers%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20could%20easily%20threaten%20a%20variety%20of%20ships.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20made%20major%20additions%20to%20its%20stockpile%20of%20an%20anti-ship%20ballistic%20missile%20sometimes%20referred%20to%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcarrier%20killer%2C%26quot%3B%20indicating%20its%20role%20in%20a%20potential%20conflict%20would%20almost%20certainly%20be%20beyond%20just%20flattops%2C%20a%20defense%20expert%20noted%20following%20the%20release%20of%20a%20new%20Pentagon%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Defense%20released%20its%20annual%20China%20Military%20Power%20Report%20to%20Congress%20analyzing%20the%20People's%20Republic%20of%20China's%20growing%20military%20might%20and%20combat%20capability.%20The%20update%20includes%20estimates%20on%20Chinese%20missile%20stockpiles%2C%20which%20show%20significant%20increases%20across%20the%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20shows%20that%20in%202022%2C%20China%20increased%20the%20number%20of%20intermediate-range%20ballistic%20missiles%20from%20300%20in%202021%20to%20500.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20DF-26%20IRBM%20has%20an%20estimated%20range%20of%201%2C000-3%2C000%20km%2C%20putting%20US%20forces%20in%20Guam%20within%20reach.%20The%20range%20earned%20the%20missile%20the%20nickname%20%26quot%3BGuam%20Killer%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BGuam%20Express%26quot%3B%20for%20its%20potential%20to%20hit%20US%20forces%20on%20the%20island%20with%20either%20nuclear%20or%20conventional%20payloads%2C%20but%20the%20weapon%20also%20has%20an%20anti-ship%20role%2C%20which%20is%20where%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bcarrier%20killer%26quot%3B%20comes%20from.%20That%20anti-ship%20role%20could%20include%20more%20than%20carriers%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20an%20increase%20in%20DF-26%20stockpile%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20China%20is%20clearly%20investing%20in%20a%20capability%20that%20can%20defeat%20defenses%20and%20effectively%20batter%20a%20variety%20of%20targets.%20That%20could%20spell%20trouble%20for%20not%20only%20US%20aircraft%20carriers%20that%20the%20People's%20Liberation%20Army%20Rocket%20Force%20(PLARF)%20would%20target%20should%20the%20two%20titans%20go%20to%20war%20but%20also%20other%20American%20ships%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227022%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20aircraft%20carrier%20USS%20Theodore%20Roosevelt%20(CVN%2071)%20transits%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536c2ef96f7540cd06342d0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223950%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20aircraft%20carrier%20USS%20Theodore%20Roosevelt%20(CVN%2071)%20transits%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean.%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Navy%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20about%20250%20launchers%20that%20are%20able%20to%20be%20reloaded%2C%C2%A0as%20there%20are%20an%20estimated%20two%20missiles%20for%20every%20launcher%2C%20meaning%20China%20could%20quickly%20overwhelm%20an%20adversary's%20defenses%20with%20a%20barrage%20of%20DF-26s%2C%20which%20China%20says%20is%20capable%20against%20large%20and%20medium-size%20ships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20said%20for%20years%20that%20if%20each%20DF-26%20launcher%20had%20just%20one%20reload%2C%20we%20could%20be%20facing%20400%2B%20missiles.%20Well%2C%20here%20we%20are%E2%80%A6%2C%26quot%3B%C2%A0Tom%20Shugart%2C%20a%20former%20US%20Navy%20submarine%20commander%20who's%20now%20an%20adjunct%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20a%20New%20American%20Security%20think%20tank%2C%20wrote%20Monday%20on%20X%2C%20the%20social%20media%20platform%20formally%20known%20as%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNumbers%20like%20that%20could%20change%20the%20DF-26%20from%20a%20'carrier%20killer'%20to%20just%20a%20'ship%20killer%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DF-26%20missile%20was%20first%20unveiled%20at%20China's%202015%20parade%20commemorating%20the%20end%20of%20World%20War%20II%20and%20has%20quickly%20become%20one%20of%20the%20more%20concerning%20missiles%20in%20its%20inventory%2C%C2%A0as%20it%20allows%20China%20to%20keep%20the%20US%20Navy%20at%20arms%20length.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20exactly%20how%20effective%20the%20missile%20is%20and%20there's%20some%20question%20marks%20on%20testing.%20The%20Pentagon%20said%20that%20in%202020%20China%20%26quot%3Bfired%20anti-ship%20ballistic%20missiles%20against%20a%20moving%20target%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20but%20has%20not%20acknowledged%20doing%20so.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202021%2C%20satellite%20photos%20showed%20apparent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-built-us-warship-mock-ups-for-possible-target-practice-2021-11%5C%22%3Efull-scale%20outlines%20of%20US%20Navy%20aircraft%20carriers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Ruoqiang%20area%20of%20Xinjiang's%20Taklamakan%20desert%20in%20northwestern%20China%2C%20an%20area%20that%20has%20reportedly%20been%20used%20previously%20for%20missile%20strike%20training.%20It%20makes%20sense%20for%20PRC%20to%20target%20US%20carriers%2C%20which%20regularly%20and%20routinely%20patrol%20waters%20and%20conduct%20exercises%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%20and%20Western%20Pacific.%20DF-26s%20give%20China%20the%20opportunity%20to%20target%20those%20carriers%20from%20a%20safe%20distance%2C%20threatening%20the%20US%20presence%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20region%20and%20specifically%20around%20Taiwan%20and%20Japan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223456%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22DF-26%20missiles%20attend%20the%20military%20parade%20in%20Beijing%2C%20capital%20of%20China%2C%20Sept.%203%2C%202015.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536c9ea96908fd7cdb57390%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222304%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDF-26%20missiles%20attend%20the%20military%20parade%20in%20Beijing%2C%20capital%20of%20China%2C%20Sept.%203%2C%202015.%3Cp%3EXinhua%2FCha%20Chunming%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20China%20is%20prioritizing%20bulking%20up%20its%20DF-26%20stockpile%2C%20as%20the%20Pentagon%20report%20indicates%2C%20that%20could%20reveal%20more%20about%20PLARF's%20potential%20aims%20in%20a%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Shugart%20wrote%20in%20August%202021%2C%20%26quot%3Bwithout%20doubt%2C%20in%20a%20war%20at%20sea%20the%20PLA%2C%20if%20it%20had%20the%20inventory%20to%20do%20so%2C%20would%20be%20perfectly%20happy%20to%20trade%20a%20missile%20(or%20several)%2C%20costing%20perhaps%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcsbaonline.org%2Fuploads%2Fdocuments%2FLeveling_the_Playing_Field_web_Final_1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20order%20of%20US%2420%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20each%2C%20for%20a%20destroyer%20that%20would%20cost%20billions%20to%20replace.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20China%20has%20that%20large%20of%20an%20inventory%20of%20anti-ship%20ballistic%20missiles%2C%20Shugart%20wrote%2C%20that%20%26quot%3Bcould%20broaden%20the%20PLARF's%20anti-ship%20mission%20from%20what%20has%20been%20thought%20of%20as%20a%20'carrier-killer'%20role%20to%20a%20more%20generic%20'ship-killer'%20mission%26quot%3B%20at%20sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20added%20strike%20capacity%20could%20be%C2%A0%20an%20additional%20challenge%20for%20the%20US%20Navy%20in%20a%20conflict%20with%20China%2C%20which%20has%20a%20naval%20force%20that%20is%20already%20larger%20than%20the%20US%20Navy%20and%20continues%20to%20grow%20in%20size%20and%20capability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-growing-df-26-missile-arsenal-more-than-carrier-killers-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698096543000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536bc0b0487ff031cabf4a9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-growing-df-26-missile-arsenal-more-than-carrier-killers-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20new%20Pentagon%20report%20shows%20major%20increases%20in%20China's%20missile%20stockpiles%2C%20including%20the%20mid-range%20DF-26%2C%20sometimes%20referred%20to%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcarrier%20killer.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cpanella%40insider.com%20(Chris%20Panella)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A33%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-growing-df-26-missile-arsenal-more-than-carrier-killers-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Amazon%20says%20bottles%20allegedly%20containing%20delivery%20drivers'%20urine%20listed%20as%20energy%20drink%20on%20its%20website%20was%20a%20'crude%20stunt'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221189%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Oobah%20Butler%20said%20he%20listed%20Amazon%20drivers'%20urine%20on%20the%20site.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65369f7896f7540cd06316d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22891%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOobah%20Butler%20said%20he%20listed%20Amazon%20drivers'%20urine%20on%20the%20site.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Oobah%20Butler%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EOobah%20Butler%20says%20he%20was%20able%20to%20list%20and%20sell%20Amazon%20drivers'%20urine%20on%20the%20marketplace.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EButler%20said%20that%20he%20marketed%20the%20urine%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bbitter%20lemon%26quot%3B%20energy%20drink%20called%20%26quot%3BRelease.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EAn%20Amazon%20spokesperson%20called%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bcrude%20stunt%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20no%20%26quot%3Bgenuine%20customer%26quot%3B%20bought%20the%20product.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20allowed%20a%20user%20on%20its%20site%20to%20sell%20bottles%20of%20its%20drivers'%20urine%20that%20were%20marketed%20as%20an%20energy%20drink%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.channel4.com%2Fprogrammes%2Fthe-great-amazon-heist%2Fon-demand%2F74583-001%5C%22%3EChannel%204%20documentary.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20documentary%20%26quot%3BThe%20Great%20American%20Heist%2C%26quot%3B%20filmmaker%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vice.com%2Fen%2Farticle%2F434gqw%2Fi-made-my-shed-the-top-rated-restaurant-on-tripadvisor%5C%22%3Epast%20prankster%20Oobah%20Butler%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20he%20collected%20discarded%20bottles%20of%20Amazon%20drivers'%20urine%20to%20sell%20on%20the%20ecommerce%20site%20and%20titled%20the%20drink%20%26quot%3BRelease.%26quot%3B%20Butler%20said%20the%20drink%20became%20the%20top%20seller%20on%20Amazon's%20%26quot%3BBitter%20Lemon%26quot%3B%20category%20and%20the%20product%20was%20made%20from%20bottles%20or%20urine%20that%20he%20found%20discarded%20near%20Amazon%20fulfillment%20centers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Amazon%20spokesperson%20called%20Release%20a%20%26quot%3Bcrude%20stunt%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20no%20%26quot%3Bgenuine%20customer%26quot%3B%20bought%20the%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSafety%20is%20a%20top%20priority%20for%20Amazon%20and%20we%20require%20all%20products%20offered%20in%20our%20store%20to%20comply%20with%20applicable%20laws%20and%20regulations%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20industry-leading%20tools%20to%20prevent%20genuinely%20unsafe%20products%20being%20listed%20and%20we%20monitor%20our%20stores%20for%20genuine%20product%20safety%20concerns.%20Any%20sellers%20who%20circumvent%20these%20policies%20will%20face%20action.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EButler%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Famazon-let-its-drivers-urine-be-sold-as-an-energy-drink%2F%23intcid%3D_wired-verso-hp-trending_f565265d-9362-4113-a045-d03f49f80bc8_popular4-1%5C%22%3Etold%20WIRED%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bsurprisingly%20easy%26quot%3B%20to%20get%20the%20product%20listed%20on%20the%20site%20and%20Amazon's%20algorithm%20moved%20the%20product%20into%20its%20drinks%20category%20on%20the%20site%20after%20he'd%20put%20it%20in%20the%20%26quot%3BRefillable%20Pump%20Dispenser%26quot%3B%20category.%20While%20Butler%20got%20some%20friends%20to%20purchase%20the%20product%20and%20never%20sold%20the%20item%20to%20any%20real%20customers%2C%20he%20told%20Insider%20he%20estimated%20that%20he%20had%20about%2010%20genuine%20customers%20who%20tried%20to%20buy%20the%20product%20on%20Amazon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERelease%20has%20since%20been%20taken%20off%20the%20Amazon%20marketplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221325%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Release%20was%20listed%20on%20Amazon%2C%20but%20has%20since%20been%20taken%20down.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536c4dd96f7540cd06344c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERelease%20was%20listed%20on%20Amazon%2C%20but%20has%20since%20been%20taken%20down.%3Cp%3EWayBack%20Machine%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20heart%20of%20Release%20Energy's%20story%20lies%20a%20dedication%20to%20empowering%20Amazon%20delivery%20drivers%2C%20unsung%20heroes%20who%20face%20immense%20pressures%20navigating%20impossibly%20demanding%20schedules%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20portion%20of%20Release's%20production%20description%20reads.%20%26quot%3BTasked%20with%20impossibly%20tight%20deadlines%2C%20these%20drivers%20find%20themselves%20in%20a%20relentless%20race%20against%20time%2C%20often%20sacrificing%20their%20own%20needs%20to%20ensure%20packages%20reach%20their%20destinations.%20Release%20Energy%20was%20born%20from%20the%20desperation%20and%20determination%20of%20those%20Amazon%20delivery%20drivers%20who%20dared%20to%20have%20bodily%20movements%20over%20the%20course%20of%20their%20gruelling%20shifts%2C%20who%20found%20themselves%20faced%20with%20a%20choice%20between%20fulfilling%20their%20contractual%20obligations%20and%20finding%20a%20bathroom.%20Each%20Release%20Energy%20drink%20is%20entirely%20comprised%20of%20their%20urine%2C%20as%20it%20was%20found%20decanted%20into%20bottles%20and%20discarded%20by%20the%20side%20of%20the%20road.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3Cp%3EButler%20told%20Insider%20he%20decided%20to%20make%20the%20documentary%20and%20try%20to%20list%20the%20bottles%20on%20Amazon%20to%20help%20shed%20some%20light%20on%20the%20company's%20impact%20on%20society%2C%20including%20on%20its%20workers%20w