0in%20quantitative%20tightening%20mode%20and%20no%20longer%20sucking%20up%20bonds%2C%20just%20as%20governments%20are%20issuing%20massive%20amounts%20of%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20all%20G7%20governments%20are%20selling%20a%20glut%20of%20bonds%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Wieladek%20added.%20And%20without%20central%20banks%2C%20who%20are%20less%20sensitive%20to%20returns%2C%20the%20bond%20market%20is%20dictated%20more%20by%20investors%20who%20are%20more%20sensitive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20this%20new%20world%2C%20bond%20supply%20can%20affect%20the%20level%20of%20yields%20through%20term%20premia%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20argued.%20%26quot%3BA%20rise%20in%20outstanding%20bonds%20will%20raise%20the%20share%20of%20private%20sector%20ownership%2C%20as%20central%20banks%20are%20not%20in%20the%20market%20any%20more.%20But%20private%20sector%20investors%20have%20many%20other%20options%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20purchasing%20bonds.%20So%20yields%20have%20to%20rise%20to%20become%20more%20attractive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20example%20of%20the%20influence%20private%20investors%20are%20now%20wielding%20in%20the%20bond%20market%2C%20Wieladek%20pointed%20to%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Ftreasury-bond-auction-us-debt-crisis-fed-buying-quantitative-tightening-2023-10%5C%22%3ETreasury%20bond%20auction%20that%20saw%20weak%20demand%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20sold%20%2420%20billion%20of%2030-year%20bonds%2C%20but%20dealers%20had%20to%20take%20up%20more%20supply%20after%20investors%20balked.%20That%20sent%20long-term%20yields%20sharply%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Ftreasury-bond-crash-yields-auction-demand-market-supply-us-debt-2023-10%5C%22%3Esubsequent%20auction%20saw%20improved%20demand%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20massive%20federal%20deficits%20going%20forward%20mean%20the%20US%20must%20continue%20flooding%20th